comments: Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) lowers his right arm and marginal contact occurs with McCollum's (NOP) right arm as he makes the pass.
Pokusevski (OKC) brushes Hayes' (NOP) left arm and Hayes is able to move through the marginal contact to finish at the rim.
Marshall (NOP) rests his right hand on Dort's (OKC) left side and marginal contact occurs as Dort drives into the lane.
McCollum (NOP) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it prior to incidental contact occurring with Williams' (OKC) left side/arm in the lane.
Marshall (NOP) initiates contact across Williams' (OKC) left arm during his upward shooting motion.
Dort (OKC) and McCollum (NOP) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Dort (OKC) briefly has his arms around Hayes' (NOP) upper half before correcting.
Hayes (NOP) establishes himself in Dort's (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Jones (NOP) and Williams (OKC) come together at the same spot along the perimeter and marginal contact occurs.
Jones (NOP) brings his right arm forward slightly and marginal contact occurs with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) left arm/side as he changes direction inside the lane.
Jones (NOP) cleanly blocks Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Pokusevski (OKC) grasps and then quickly releases Hayes' (NOP) shorts during rebounding.

Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) turns with his right hand extended forward and he initiates contact with Jones' (NOP) front, affecting Jones' SQBR in transition. The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime. After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that the foul by Gilgeous-Alexander does not meet the criteria for a clear path foul.
Murphy III (NOP) turns slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Williams (OKC) at the end of the drive.
Murphy III (NOP) contests the layup attempt and marginal contact occurs with Williams' (OKC) arm after the release.
Dort (OKC) goes to, not through, Hayes' (NOP) space and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the pick.
Hayes (NOP) establishes a slightly wide screening position and absorbs the contact with Dort (OKC) to his upper body before some lower body contact occurs.
Pokusevski (OKC) turns with his left leg extended forward and he initiates contact with McCollum's (NOP) right leg, affecting McCollum's SQBR at the end of the drive.
Williams (OKC) brushes McCollum's (NOP) left wrist and marginal contact occurs after McCollum gathers the ball.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) jumps forward slightly and marginal body contact occurs during Jones' (NOP) shot attempt near the rim.
Jones (NOP) and Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.

McCollum (NOP) brings his left arm forward and marginal contact occurs with Mann's (OKC) slightly extended left arm after his gather. McCollum then turns slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Mann during the driving shot attempt.
Hayes (NOP) and Pokusevski (OKC) each make clean contact with the ball prior to any incidental arm contact occurring during rebounding.

The game is stopped due to the shot clock expiring. After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that the ball hit the rim and that more than 25.4 seconds expired after the start of the possession. The game would go to overtime.
Jones (NOP) briefly has his arm around Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) midsection before correcting.
Jones (NOP) is moving alongside Giddey's (OKC) path and absorbs the marginal body contact as they come together prior to Giddey losing control of the ball.
McCollum (NOP) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Giddey (OKC) at the end of the drive.
McCollum (NOP) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two steps before releasing the pass.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) initiates contact across Hayes' (NOP) left arm during his upward shooting motion.
Williams (OKC) establishes his left foot as his pivot and slides it in the corner.
Dort (OKC) brushes Marshall's (NOP) left arm and marginal contact occurs after Marshall's gather.
McCollum (NOP) cleanly blocks Giddey's (OKC) shot attempt near the rim.
Marshall (NOP) brushes Dort's (OKC) left arm and marginal contact occurs after Dort's gather. Jones (NOP) legally contests Dort's driving shot attempt thereafter.
McCollum (NOP) brushes Williams' (OKC) front after the release of his jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs.
McCollum (NOP) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Williams (OKC) is turning away from Jones (NOP) and avoids making contact with Jones' front after his gather.
Hayes (NOP) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Williams (OKC) and McCollum (NOP) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Williams (OKC) attempts to commit a take foul on Hayes (NOP) and marginal contact occurs with Hayes' front after he releases the pass.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) commits a take foul on Marshall (NOP).
Jones (NOP) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Pokusevski (OKC) as Pokusevski makes the pass.
Murphy III (NOP) is moving alongside Giddey's (OKC) path and marginal body contact occurs after Giddey's gather.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: McCollum (NOP) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Jones (NOP) goes to, not through, Pokusevski's (OKC) space and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the screen.

Pokusevski (OKC) turns slightly as he braces for the impending contact with Jones (NOP) and absorbs it as it occurs during the screen.
Murphy III (NOP) legally contests Joe's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Giddey (OKC) and Hayes (NOP) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
